timeline.bodyText:
It seems odd that you need to create a resolver for each file. Do you want to process the same schema multiple times if it is referenced by other schemas? Consider this scenario:
Prev:
A.pdl:
record A {
b: B
}
B.pdl:
record B {
f1: int
f2: float
}
Current:
A.pdl:
record A {
b: B
}
B.pdl:
record B {
f1: int
// f2 deleted
}
Now will the error be reported once for B.pdl or twice, for both A.pdl and B.pdl?
I know we report the error multiple times for resource compatibility checking, but do you think that is the best options for schema checker also?

